TY  - JOUR
TI  - Multiperiod Predictions from Stochastic Difference Equations by Bayesian Methods
AU  - Chow, Gregory C.
AB  - [Given n observations on a system of linear stochastic difference equations with appropriate initial conditions, and given a prior density (possibly diffuse) of its parameters, this paper obtains the predictor of the time series k periods into the future with minimum mean squared error. Completely analytical solution is given for predictions from the first-order univariate system, and, in the general higher-order multivariate case, for k up to 5.]
